skos:Concept.skos:definition: {"id": "dc0432c8-53b0-4799-86ed-7273a92c3b2b", "value": "Disturbances caused by turning the earth to prepare the land for planting crops"}
{"id": "97d7ead8-1b5a-4bc9-95f6-d9be6f48fa3b", "value": "Listed/Registered as a an archaeological site in an official registry of sites and monuments"}
{"id": "f80cc554-57d4-446b-b923-7bd83341b756", "value": "Invasion/inhabitation by living organisms in numbers or quantities large enough to be harmful. This includes burrowing."}

{"id": "1f59c1d2-ed26-46dc-85da-317063ce7b2b", "value": "This term should be used to indicate that, given the current evidence, there is no evidence for damage and/or threat to the archaeological site mentioned in published imagery or identifiable from imagery sources."}
{"id": "4dc61145-a1d6-47c5-8cd9-1b3c91389dc1", "value": "The act of removing material (e.g. stone/mudbrick) from an archaeological site."}
{"id": "561adb63-c462-4f90-92c0-fdc58c688298", "value": "deliberate and anthropogenic act of flooding an area with water"}
{"id": "2ef1f88a-1eed-4644-a1cd-f0339c2c0b98", "value": "damage caused by the flow and movement of the water (i.e. river bank, lake, sea and coastal erosion). Different from rainfall damage"}
{"id": "6c1f3a69-3d39-4fca-8747-b479f4fb5e61", "value": "The addition of land adjacent to a waterbody as a result of sediment deposition, causing the shoreline to move seaward"}
{"id": "9f0edcb9-e817-4f02-a6bd-7f85ae6ce0eb", "value": "The action of laying a pipe or cable on, or buried into, the ground/seabed surface"}
{"id": "d322c6df-7a5d-4a07-874f-c57c76ac8ba5", "value": "An exothermic process involving the oxidation of material, sending out light and heat and possibly producing smoke."}
{"id": "965baa5a-0aab-4f08-ab8b-e44ab1e50536", "value": "Disturbances caused by animals roaming to consume vegetation"}
{"id": "e52efe2d-ad8d-4a6c-b295-d4c753ec5105", "value": "Disturbances caused by turning the earth to prepare the land for planting crops"}
{"id": "ba89d260-ad94-439d-b497-4ff9e02d14ac", "value": "Natural plants covering and disturbing sites"}

{"id": "c46c4330-50fe-4621-97ab-6d3e111f202d", "value": "The contamination of the land, water, air etc., by the presence or introduction of poisioness or harmful substances. This can cover pollution arising from natural disasters, as well as pollution caused by dense urbanization etc."}
{"id": "e8cb6688-406c-48b3-8c6d-e948961afd73", "value": "sudden movement and shaking of the surface of the earth"}

{"id": "6668b170-4263-4d66-a632-5a133bfa97f4", "value": "The deliberate act of changing the countours of the land/earth's surface. This can include landscaping in order to produce terraces, as well as the deposition of imported soil, raising the level of land surface/"}
{"id": "41704a8e-a940-4ba3-8df0-0ad26ec69f03", "value": "Any damage or wear associated with tourism related activities such as footfall erosion, rubbish, infrastructure etc."}
{"id": "85facaf8-5964-4ee1-a8c2-949ee52e097d", "value": "Activities related to armed and/or military forces"}

{"id": "cd202414-2de3-4c80-b377-c25f9656b338", "value": "Salt dissolved in groundwater (or sometimes water from the air) raising up and recrystallizing in heritage features such as buildings or rock surfaces."}

{"id": "bb3055f3-ee90-41d1-a998-71545cbcc9fe", "value": "Shifts in the environmental conditions at a site/of a feature. This definition would include changes in moisture content at both a local and regional level, as well as shifts in the comparative scales of hot and cold."}
{"id": "948e1b2b-5510-4be6-866e-d7c862c06bde", "value": "A path or route leading from one place to another, often including a built or anthropogenically modified/altered surface"}
{"id": "fa6f1ca9-ac49-433d-8afe-be2c48c96919", "value": "The release of energy in an often sudden and violent way. This can lead to the sudden shattering or blowing apart of objects/features."}
{"id": "8cf0bc64-f931-4c85-817f-597d63463b29", "value": "Damage and wear associated with failure of care"}
{"id": "2784f7db-dd6a-4bbf-945e-58a61e5560d1", "value": "Inappropriate use or inhabitation of ancient structures"}
{"id": "a2323aa5-7ab5-43c0-be57-eba145db6a0a", "value": "The collapse/movement of a mass of earth or rock, generally down a slope."}
{"id": "21200da6-6d2c-4b8f-a14e-919091aa988a", "value": "The act of clearing and/or flattening/destroying ground or archaeological features/modern buildings etc., by hand/using handtools"}
{"id": "5e490535-fa6c-4893-ab4a-a9c7bb4acd6b", "value": "Disturbances caused by building structures at domestic or industrial scale"}
{"id": "bc300701-95dc-48db-9b0a-1aac2de6b997", "value": "The excavation or clearance of the bed of a waterbody, using heavy machinery"}
{"id": "6660cfcf-5a34-4641-9a5e-53ef42f8f1f7", "value": "Infrastructure development related to supplying services and facilities and transport development specifically roads, railway, and bridges."}
{"id": "5857557b-fc1c-499d-ad1e-4aac73104365", "value": "Disturbances caused by any construction on the site, especially built and used to store manure"}
{"id": "ac2a9ec8-144d-4129-8e2b-9aaf2a239a86", "value": "Constructing toilet on the site"}

{"id": "f889a8b0-a207-414b-be4a-3b5b76c4db0d", "value": "A prolonged period of abnormally low rainfall, leading to a shortage of water; for heritage sites the decreased humidity can cause structural and other problems. For normally submerged sites use \"Recession of water\"."}
{"id": "9d940ecb-1692-4c55-9809-06011cf956cf", "value": "damages caused by the natural overflow of water that submerges archaeological sites and features."}

{"id": "93ed9ae7-6f74-466f-9336-6b78e27b9aae", "value": "The act of making a hole using a boring or rotating mechanism. Drilling can be associated with activities such as Oil extraction and the sinking of well systems."}
{"id": "2fd7cbf7-048b-473a-a171-b32d1c25b37e", "value": "Disturbances caused by the rearing of animals"}
{"id": "c2dec037-2c29-45b6-814b-c804d3098ba8", "value": "artificial navigable wayer ways and any other contemporary built water feature/structure disturbing the site"}
{"id": "acfac2d9-5cd6-4d59-b122-5b0c7970a23c", "value": "The artificial act of supplying water by way of digging trenches, drains, centre pivot system, etc. across a landscape"}
{"id": "c4584981-f22f-47c5-8f83-aa1580e1be6b", "value": "The loss of land adjacent to a waterbody as a result of sediment removal, causing the shoreline to move landward"}
{"id": "0b7184ed-3e77-4421-8846-8448b99b418b", "value": "dumping of rubbish or waste on archaeological sites"}
{"id": "eb1bcc42-2180-4e72-ba9b-b6f812e16ae5", "value": "deliberate destruction, damage, or writing/drawing on an archaeological site, feature, or object"}
{"id": "9b82293a-8a99-4176-841f-f34701bbe445", "value": "Lowering or complete disappearance of the surface elevation of a lake or other water body (e.g. sea)"}
{"id": "07b6e38e-f706-4e85-9435-33780c918862", "value": "Disturbances caused by digging a trench or a hole by bulldozer for any purpose other than mining/quarrying"}

{"id": "8032df36-2edb-401e-bca9-2406d4e2a065", "value": "Damage and wear associated with the absence of considered preservation/maintenance activities where there is a normally a possibility of care"}
{"id": "c4ea2e97-8e6e-4f08-9d5c-eb53249a1fea", "value": "Disturbances caused by farming and cultivating"}
{"id": "471fc31c-1998-4173-94c9-070a4b4da8a3", "value": "expansion/growth of housing, commercial/public buildings, and infrastructure development"}
{"id": "f59db2f3-a4d4-432b-a4fe-8c4c61506867", "value": "Damage and wear from eroding gullies of water caused by excessive/consistent rain and/or lack of drainage"}

{"id": "31a6caba-f46b-4058-a94c-427d706c9328", "value": "The act of destruction or tearing down of archaeological structures. This act can be carried out both in a controlled and uncontrolled manner, but also using both mechanised and/or hand machinery"}
{"id": "4cca64ac-cb7b-4317-8ecc-b32ed5fb7439", "value": "The act of people walking on and moving across a heritage site or feature causing damage to the features"}

{"id": "b9fb0d5d-1ce9-4d84-bd9a-b493f138cc14", "value": "The act of living, inhabiting or continuing to utilise a heritage place. Use only the occupation causes negative effects and damage to the site"}
{"id": "f02c358f-c997-4aa5-858b-4820dea71dac", "value": "A land/areas used for burial of human remains expanding or built over archaeological site"}
{"id": "ebff70cc-a12d-4efb-a608-73c2f41b9468", "value": "Digging narrow channels through earth"}

{"id": "97d18fca-4ba3-44c2-8912-672f83c6d4d9", "value": "Disturbances caused by the removal of heritage materials and objects from archaeological/heritage sites and museums; this term should be used for digging looting holes/pits in archaeological sites or the removal of objects and features from sites and museums"}
{"id": "434834c0-9395-4880-8b18-3d1e574e1aa0", "value": "Changing land topography to create a desired terrain surface mainly for agricultural purposes/needs"}
{"id": "40ec4be9-f7d3-4147-b272-ecd0c49f7ce2", "value": "Activities related to the farming of land and/or the rearing of animals"}
{"id": "abdfb266-49ab-4821-a9fc-08b416547955", "value": "weathering as a cause of erosion of sites and structures due to wind, rainfall or change of weather"}
{"id": "5534c4ef-85c3-4942-a9de-b44f2cdc06d3", "value": "Damage from the creation or proximity to waterways, drain, gully or stream of water"}
{"id": "18d22bb4-6ee4-45ef-8d04-878e74ee4048", "value": "Damage caused by conservation/intervention where some activity has taken place attempting to preserve the site but has instead caused harm"}
{"id": "c57900f9-24a0-44c4-a1ce-f969aa998460", "value": "The collapse/movement of a mass of earth or rock, generally down a slope."}
{"id": "2ee51407-a37d-4143-b215-1370793b0a08", "value": "Transparent, hard substance made by fusing soda-silica which solidifies from a molten state."}
{"id": "7a72516f-069f-4720-bfa3-55efcfd93959", "value": "A land surface inclined at an angle. Slopes are the flanks of valleys and the edges of uplands."}
{"id": "b05a14e1-2c44-4737-ac61-49541333790c", "value": "The extent of site/feature has been mapped in the field (either primary or secondary sources)"}

{"id": "12621403-d552-4461-b31e-f4562d0ce5fc", "value": "The site/feature has a diffuse boundary (i.e. it is hard to identify from imagery where the site starts and ends). It appears to have a different extent on different images. Alternatively, if the extent of site (mound site) is drawn from Survey of India historic map or if the site is listed by published sources it is only referred to using very broad size categories e.g. 0-5ha."}

{"id": "9f9d425a-f0ab-40cb-9ea4-8daa6adcba34", "value": "The site/feature has a very diffuse boundary and/or appears to have a very different extent on different images, or alternatively is not visible on imagery. The site may also have no overall spatial information associated with it i.e. is only located by a broad scale map and/or by reference to a general region. In this case both the site location and site extent certainty will be negligible. This certainty level should also be used for polygons which are \"user-defined\" e.g. around a group of cairns which are not necessarily chronologically or functionally related."}

{"id": "7cb253ce-603e-4214-aadc-a408a3a343ef", "value": "The site/feature appears to have a fairly clear boundary and it is similar on multiple images. References to the site extent within published data may roughly correspond to what is identifiable via imagery."}

{"id": "36b7540a-0133-4d3c-bb4c-5e728d3ec3ec", "value": "The extent of site/feature has been mapped in the field however there may be some concern over the correspondence between the field and imagery extents OR The site/feature has a very clear boundary and is very similar on multiple images. The site, however, may not have been mapped in the field"}
{"id": "9d4b3cf6-afaa-4eb2-a90f-d1a7b993a15f", "value": "Laying stones to form a wall, bonded with mortar."}

{"id": "28594de1-8a58-4ebe-b83b-2ea2cb79fb9c", "value": "A material usually consisting of clay, sand, or other aggregate, such as sea shell, and water, which has been compressed and dried; used in building construction."}
{"id": "4e0197b6-59e5-4541-b5ad-455a1b5c3c23", "value": "Covering with a flat shaped roof"}
{"id": "e6f10ee7-565d-4e7c-a43a-996b4a6e3fdc", "value": "Double laid (masonry) wall, often of stone, filled in the middle with earth/small stone rubble"}
{"id": "63a3e6e1-c8ae-41bd-8ef3-6311ae2b473e", "value": "Covering with a vault shaped roof"}
{"id": "a74c0771-859c-49f5-b3b8-8a1690c127b9", "value": "Laying a pavement or similar surface."}

{"id": "5c89644a-263b-4a78-9968-0217ae8b90de", "value": "Walls composed of clay, earth, straw, lime and sand, mixed with water. Constructed without shutters in layers upon a stone or brick plinth. The layers are applied wet and left to dry before applying the next layer and usually covered with protective limewash"}
{"id": "cf5cf7b6-27f0-4e93-b81a-49ac135a135c", "value": "Laying stone to form a wall."}

{"id": "84d6e378-0d5c-4eba-ae12-2e3007bea1c3", "value": "The process and technique of cutting architectural works or large sculptures out of living rock rather than assembling the works from processed blocks of stone or other materials"}
{"id": "d30d981c-7190-43ef-8352-96ea7787a9c1", "value": "Structural members whose primary function is to carry transverse loads"}

{"id": "70cb25a8-6b6c-4ad1-bd19-438556aa3779", "value": "Timber/wood framed component. Wood, cut and seasoned so forming or capable of forming any part of a structure. May be treated with preservative before use."}
{"id": "e8ccf68c-1385-4b9c-be8e-411469dbee71", "value": "Construction consisting of upright posts or stakes interwoven with twigs or tree branches and plastered with a mixture of clay and straw."}
{"id": "ba960bf2-4df4-4ede-bb96-1d0911b7352e", "value": "Applying a coat on other building material to make to surface smooth."}
{"id": "cf5e5939-a70d-445b-9ae9-478e76fa8334", "value": "Overlaying a wall or floor with tiles"}
{"id": "9bb1c5f5-9d93-4907-9cc7-40fdf4944e42", "value": "Construction materials/products made of Iron/Steel"}
{"id": "cb9fbb12-e004-4f59-9500-e6fa349544f3", "value": "Covering with a dome/concave shaped roof"}
{"id": "4eb20e28-3111-45eb-a3e0-1cb2fa409b81", "value": "Laying bricks (baked bricks or dried mud bricks or breeze blocks) with mortar to form a wall"}
{"id": "5d842758-9f39-4f6f-b0a5-f90d3c2e0729", "value": "Fine plaster used for covering walls and for making decorations (cornices, mouldings, etc.)"}
{"id": "500c6b17-52b0-43d7-9313-db80f5d991df", "value": "Covering with a sloping roof"}
{"id": "e6b4a724-c8dc-4a3d-a92b-1e174917870c", "value": "Laying stones to form a wall without the use of mortar."}

{"id": "e2770238-d651-4bf6-816f-f26612ba0877", "value": "Type of tile used for roofing, usually of fired clay, slate, metal, concrete, asbestos cement, or plastic; available in many configurations and types such as plain tiles, single-lap tiles, and interlocking tiles"}
{"id": "81a7f1e3-1b09-4059-9791-3ebf74895fb0", "value": "Process of making materials or surfaces impervious to water by applying waterproof material"}
{"id": "dd0187b6-8d61-47a4-ab37-30c90baaf560", "value": "Inlaid surface decoration for floors and walls formed by small pieces of stone, glass or ceramic."}
{"id": "2ca23291-9f2b-4a5a-8b29-7f1b0a06b1da", "value": "The activities related to the extraction of natural recourses from the earth by any means"}
{"id": "f4f90ade-693d-4517-bb11-05ebd90e68ee", "value": "A piece of metal, usually cast, struck or stamped, with a definite value."}
{"id": "a9107d18-ada1-49d8-9fa7-f58b87703342", "value": "Fragment/pieces of furnaces, ovens, or heated enclosures for drying, charring, hardening, baking, or burning various materials."}
{"id": "bbdf9261-6c72-40df-ad3e-936d64b09ac9", "value": "Waste flakes and cores produced in the manufacture of stone implements."}
{"id": "8b806611-156b-4828-8f5b-45e4463639e8", "value": "An individual section of panelling. Can form fences, ceilings or an outer layer to a wall etc."}
{"id": "368b10ad-25a7-4e83-8abd-6c196578ee7a", "value": "An oblong/rectangular mass of hardened clay or mud, used in ancient and heritage buildings"}

{"id": "183ec64a-0498-42af-a8c0-348265fc5843", "value": "A piece of a larger faience object, a composite material consisting of a body of sintered quartz coupled with an alkaline glaze surface, and used for decorating beads, amulets, figurines, and other small objects."}
{"id": "14619c58-2334-496f-85f1-4dda461c926e", "value": "A stone implement that has been shaped by the action of grinding"}
{"id": "2f06dcb7-49a1-4f6c-8603-73af17d0b3a6", "value": "A construction material made by the firing or baking of clay"}
{"id": "1aa95ed3-4f0f-48b4-8e55-19a5dfffda3f", "value": "Small sculpted object depicting another object or being, made of clay"}

{"id": "4e868990-f88e-448e-9ada-1c501bbacac2", "value": "General term for a group rocks, the constituent minerals of which have assumed a position in more or less closely parallel layers due to metamorphic action. They comprise layers of lamellar minerals, such as mica, chlorite, talc, hornblende, and graphite."}
{"id": "027731a4-6b7c-45ee-85f1-527e464bdf2e", "value": "Fragments/byproducts of shell based objects and jewellry"}
{"id": "a9d35b17-e7bc-421a-84b6-9d3af221d7ac", "value": "Any of the pieces of hard tissue consisting largely of calcium phosphate that make up the skeleton of a vertebrate animal or human"}
{"id": "0c088beb-72e0-4c54-9d93-183a67ff4f0a", "value": "Material remains or byproducts of a manufacturing or other processes"}

{"id": "0f98405f-7047-4fae-82ef-a5095d4da749", "value": "Hand-operated mills typically consisting of a slab with a slightly concave upper surface and a smaller, smooth, rounded stone, used for grinding or pulverizing grains or other food materials."}

{"id": "3181894b-f960-4891-a2b3-065074393259", "value": "Flat clay surfaces or slabs, either portable or mounted on a wall or other structure, bearing or intended to bear inscriptions or pictures; also, thin, rigid slabs used as writing surfaces."}
{"id": "074b1885-50fd-44f7-a2ba-039a2b60ad47", "value": "A circular band, usually metal, worn on the finger or toe for ornamentation"}

{"id": "a5586e66-f1f8-4fb8-a397-022cae713237", "value": "An object which serves as a vessel. This class includes containers for which the function is either specific or unknown. Where the function is known, the term is also included within another class, eg churn."}
{"id": "3df6f693-62f2-4398-bee6-ba81cc139cdf", "value": "Use this category for any find that is not listed here and then use the note field to name the type of artefact you are recording"}
{"id": "34f6463a-1e5b-4033-8f26-de4c641647de", "value": "Thin, flat pieces of stone intentionally removed from a tool or core during the process of stone tool manufacture."}
{"id": "6bf242dc-0911-488c-92ae-62e65449a17e", "value": "A piece of gold, usually cast, struck or stamped, with a definite value"}

{"id": "4278d251-83a6-494b-95c8-70702d9ea0be", "value": "Clay that has undergone some kind of firing process, hardening it, whether as a byproduct or purposeful action. Clay being a naturally occurring sediments that are produced by chemical actions resulting during the weathering of rocks. Clays are composed of hydrated aluminum silicates, such as Kaolinite"}
{"id": "7c97d126-cc63-4549-910d-671f0cfa0449", "value": "Any object which bears an carving or inscription."}
{"id": "5442bb26-5733-4057-87fb-fd5088e9ec56", "value": "A small, pierced, often spherical or cylindrical piece of glass, wood etc. which may be strung together with others to form a necklace"}
{"id": "733e06f9-4c94-435d-aae2-3406f8373c21", "value": "Objects which cannot be assigned to any one particular class, or the function of which is unknown"}
{"id": "5c769303-0a3c-4c96-9841-9afe759270ff", "value": "A piece of copper, usually cast, struck or stamped, with a definite value"}
{"id": "8531b174-6106-464e-beb7-55fb664e1c4f", "value": "Fragments of a structure, usually material that has been worked"}
{"id": "f81b7665-be0d-4981-aee7-8364f35ec062", "value": "Thin, flat pieces of stone intentionally removed from a tool or core during the process of stone tool manufacture."}
{"id": "730080d0-a52e-457a-b8bd-c65f37bf3a5b", "value": "Ornamental band or chain worn around the arm or wrist."}
{"id": "879e9b99-5e5a-4dec-a359-90353636d3dd", "value": "A three dimensional representation of an object, person or animal"}
{"id": "9b7dd2d6-8a97-4f74-9f4e-9a0b60294826", "value": "Statuette or small carved/sculpted figure, usually a depiction of human, animal, diety or anthropomorphic"}
{"id": "bb7015cc-dc4b-425e-8da3-a20da5ce78fa", "value": "A refuse heap of discarded shells"}
{"id": "2ecdc10c-f06f-4ae9-9ef8-d46da848dfff", "value": "Stone used as a building material, sometimes shaped/dressed"}
{"id": "8f0f43e2-fa75-4a3a-ae4a-4fcc0e411dfa", "value": "Knapped or ground stone/flint tool where the specific type is unknown. Use more specific type where known"}

{"id": "9eaab2d3-49e1-4ee4-b0f6-0361a3a0846b", "value": "Accumulations of coins purposely buried or otherwise hidden as a group; may contain artifacts of any material or of different materials as well as different kinds of coins"}
{"id": "03b72d86-44cc-4d44-8b22-06d5bb2a6488", "value": "An appliance that produces light by means of a liquid fuel and a wick."}
{"id": "5386980d-67fc-4355-9f0d-880e1607d327", "value": "An rectangular mass of hardened clay or mud, used in modern buildings (i.e. post 1950s)"}
{"id": "79a73e91-8ca0-4436-974c-3155694ebd61", "value": "The exoskeleton of salt-water mollusks, often used for jewelry or decorative objects."}
{"id": "f6a0ade4-ca90-453c-91f1-5efc0a0def32", "value": "A byproduct of the creation of faience objects"}

{"id": "6f7432fd-6a55-4b3b-ad0c-870e2da22212", "value": "Fragment/byproduct of steatite carvings and manufactured objects. A very soft rock composed primarily of hydrated magnesium silicate (soapstone). It is easily cut and has been used for carvings."}
{"id": "1623d538-0475-4e9e-b1bc-32ce5936c3b6", "value": "A by-product usually from the smelting process."}
{"id": "498aa7dc-89fc-44ca-9a00-889c7932e7be", "value": "Process of stabilizing or reinforcing to give additional physical support, typically by adding thickness or by covering."}
{"id": "eab18de0-ef3a-40f4-8647-13789152a889", "value": "The pressing or packing down of archaeological sites/artefacts/soils and so the material becomes flattened and/or compressed."}
{"id": "adc70430-969c-4835-99ec-6ce6c7d918aa", "value": "The face or front of a building towards outside."}
{"id": "d722b755-0aa9-4fe0-842e-e5e968d8452a", "value": "Cultivated plant covering the ground in the field survey (a opposed to exposed ground surface)"}
{"id": "b13419aa-f4b2-44d1-95c9-a2fea28b4f1d", "value": "removing dirt, debris and altered products from the surface of recorded heritage"}

{"id": "0221b145-63bf-44ef-b03c-d56127cc5934", "value": "The site/Feature has been identified on historic map. It is also identifiable on imagery, although there may be some concern over its 'shifting location' in different imagery sets. This may be due to poor imagery, rectification issues and/or limited data. Location coordinates in Degrees, Minutes, Seconds or Decimal Degrees."}

{"id": "476297e8-ca1e-4043-bc27-686cf55110a5", "value": "Handheld GPS device capable of receiving information from Global Positioning System (GPS) satellites and then calculate the device's geographical position."}

{"id": "5484238b-c494-4908-a558-dca065b8e923", "value": "The contamination of the land, water, air etc., by the presence or introduction of poisioness or harmful substances. This can cover pollution arising from natural disasters, as well as pollution caused by dense urbanization etc."}

{"id": "2b712c96-2805-4a63-a667-bb8975b3006d", "value": "A stone or boulder which has been deliberately set upright in the ground. Use only for isolated stones. Otherwise use specific type where known."}

{"id": "4992d355-6f17-40cc-81fb-496dbd6a1ddf", "value": "Designates buildings or groups of buildings that are abandoned by their owners, often constituting potential public hazards. In a legal connotations, the term does not include buildings that are temporarily vacant or unoccupied"}

{"id": "d8586a26-9ed2-4b3f-a3db-c67462ff3a96", "value": "Buddhist commemorative monument, normally hemispherical"}

{"id": "0718f020-65c0-4588-b627-9128470a76e1", "value": "An area of land enclosed by a boundary ditch, bank, wall, palisade or other similar barrier"}

{"id": "a24013f9-b987-4830-91c9-a5178d6264ab", "value": "Buildings that are significant in the history of architecture, that incorporate significant architectural features, or that played significant historic roles in local cultural or social development; may or may not be officially designated. For buildings that are abandoned but not considered necessarily historic, use \"abandoned buildings.\""}

{"id": "54577286-6188-418d-9918-777003c2092b", "value": "A structure used for raw material processing. It could be fueled by water or wind"}
{"id": "c1ef8b96-cd76-492c-8d06-d66d35300f95", "value": "Entry/Exit point associated with a larger structure or wall. Can be monumental in form."}
{"id": "1dac7609-4fde-4147-9a83-52166220a17b", "value": "A layer of brick, stone, wood, mosaic, etc. on the ground on which people walk."}
{"id": "1e7b9a81-8525-411a-9a0a-19dd632dcf36", "value": "A building used for Christian worship"}
{"id": "40619b86-6b15-41de-b754-dd6b58031a6a", "value": "Refers to massively large stones, especially those very roughly worked or left as found; used in various ancient monuments"}

{"id": "b4a11e0a-9068-4996-84a8-c35ad1b56480", "value": "A place with temporary/seasonal accommodation (e.g. huts/tents)"}
{"id": "a8a8e199-3ab4-4f7b-a1ff-381b02b15464", "value": "Usually a single standing pillar or upright structure that marks a route, distance or territory"}
{"id": "7fb8bfdb-2672-4db3-9386-6510888e1407", "value": "A structure designed for spiritual or religious activities/worship"}
{"id": "091d85a4-e182-4dff-bda4-3459a13aa6c6", "value": "Structures spanning and providing passage over waterways, topographic depressions, transportation routes, or similar circulation barriers."}
{"id": "262f1d6d-1e30-4b82-9855-9910c73b86ed", "value": "A building for human habitation, especially a dwelling place. Use more specific type where known"}
{"id": "162c21a3-f36a-4299-adae-ed9bb672a640", "value": "Structures and features designed to control the flow and movement of water"}

{"id": "706a0367-5058-405f-996b-168b0fdb17dd", "value": "Three-dimensional works of art in which images and forms are produced in relief, in intaglio, or in the round. The term refers particularly to art works created by carving or engraving a hard material, by molding or casting a malleable material (which usually then hardens), or by assembling parts to create a three-dimensional object. It is typically used to refer to large or medium-sized objects made of stone, wood, bronze, or another metal. Small objects are typically referred to as \"carvings\" or another appropriate term. \"Sculpture\" refers to works that represent tangible beings, objects, or groups of objects, or are abstract works that have defined edges and boundaries and can be measured."}
{"id": "44b7ff75-1184-4923-9323-084df3ca03e4", "value": "Tall, often narrow, structure that is either free standing or part of a larger structure. In some cases could function as 'Watch Tower'."}
{"id": "893cbdd2-7329-49df-8b3d-809a35c596bc", "value": "An area of land associated with burials of the dead"}
{"id": "6ba53428-6f05-427a-ae7d-f60add22db3e", "value": "Locations where a hostile meetings of opposing military forces in the course of a war have taken place"}
{"id": "ff394f20-e4a2-42aa-8eb6-4b7bdde8b9de", "value": "A building/place with religious importance because of its association with divinity/sacred person/relic. May have a burial/relic of a saint"}
{"id": "3567e5e5-fa4f-4147-be4b-c50eb1043d62", "value": "A conglomeration of structures that make up a religious site e.g. stupas, temples, monastery, etc."}

{"id": "37c6db75-76b6-4a55-9e41-852331fb6766", "value": "Piles of earth heaped up for landmarks, monuments, or as bases for other structures; for piles of earth and other debris resulting from successive superimposed occupation sites, use \"Settlement/Habitation Site.\" For piles of earth built over grave sites, use \"burial mounds.\" Use \"cairns\" for purposely erected piles of stones."}
{"id": "0bef89f0-0330-4c7a-a3eb-3e0167c31ab4", "value": "A building equipped with facilities for bathing, and occasionally public baths"}
{"id": "61936fdf-1e16-4b90-85fa-50c3af34379d", "value": "An area of land including farm building and features, specifically used for agricultural and animal rearing."}

{"id": "dd87e0d9-cd04-4b52-81bc-0131fa99daea", "value": "A building or a complex of buildings/town designed and built for defense"}

{"id": "554a62ad-19cc-4480-a97a-b5cd4a68e907", "value": "A structure or place on which a fire is made and is designed for cooking or processing food"}
{"id": "5b7f9ae0-4559-494d-9f26-33295e40141e", "value": "A building (or complex of buildings) used for the residence of elite or high-ranking leaders"}

{"id": "39b12167-147e-43fa-adde-e164322e20e4", "value": "A place where people live and containing traces of human habitation. A settlement can range from a group of dwellings to large cities. In South Asia context a Settlement Mound could be called 'Dheri', 'Khera', 'Pur' used as prefix or suffix."}

{"id": "31984e8f-a0e7-4831-8dd4-09be6f0c3dff", "value": "Piles of earth erected over grave sites; for piles of stones built over grave sites, use \"cairns\"; for piles of earth used generally and not over burials, use \"mounds.\""}

{"id": "bf0afb63-fd60-4af5-aade-6513c204147c", "value": "The remains of buildings or groups of buildings that have been destroyed or are in a state of great disrepair or decay"}
{"id": "39653f71-6395-428a-8aae-bc2fa5f02ed8", "value": "A structure/enclosure for keeping and providing shelter for animals"}

{"id": "d5a9dac6-138c-4d8e-91f2-9f769de3bcb7", "value": "Built complexes for religious retirement or seclusion from the world for monks, who are people living a celibate life according to the rule of a particular religious order and adhering to vows, especially of poverty, chastity, and obedience."}
{"id": "b174c7e5-9886-47dc-8f0b-fdafcba3e485", "value": "A structure used for the making (burring, baking, or drying) of pottery, lime or metal"}
{"id": "d33e0bc8-db5f-4f7e-852c-b5e445a2ef7c", "value": "A barrier of concrete or earth, etc, built across a river to create a reservoir of water for domestic and/or industrial usage."}
{"id": "3ec415d3-29da-4040-b1ba-22b4cd6b34e1", "value": "A group of lands/fields, often enclosed, used for agricultural and animal grazing which form a coherent unit"}

{"id": "50b1b555-06f6-4419-906b-548e6122d392", "value": "The polygon indicates the extent of a buffer zone usually an area surrounding the site which has the complementary legal and/or customary restrictions placed on its use and development in order to give an added layer of protection to the site"}
{"id": "0b66d3f0-932f-42f6-bb90-872a7dd924aa", "value": "Lines (a polygon) marking the legal and official limits of a site/an area"}
{"id": "c16f7083-0092-4b93-87bf-163d0c29678e", "value": "Only to be used for sites without any geometry"}
{"id": "ebf7bbbd-af28-4f2f-955c-c70b6a1f364a", "value": "A fixed point location to which all measurments on a site are calibrated"}

{"id": "6e18e4b1-b341-453a-ac21-1763f8f3a2a8", "value": "A polygon marking the known (horizontal) extent of the heritage location. The extent of the site could be drawn based on field survey data (more accurate) or what can be seen on satellite imagery"}

{"id": "4f36d755-ee1a-452c-89de-042f9a2b610c", "value": "Approximate location point of the site when the exact location of the site is not known, or a point in the vicinity of the site where the site itself cannot be reached"}
{"id": "66baf823-b861-484c-a385-8b10813c6171", "value": "A single coordinate indicating the location of the site"}

{"id": "272ae938-559c-4592-ae95-81ed7b347ea1", "value": "A structure, consisting of a curved top, that holds the weight of something above it or merely ornamental."}
{"id": "29b646a2-23ce-4207-a934-0454e0af9c80", "value": "An internal part of the building separated by walls, floor and ceiling."}

{"id": "96ff26f6-6a3f-42ad-b542-f36fba07653f", "value": "Feature/place associated with facilities and or services which are predominantly economically orientated or mercantile in nature."}

{"id": "723d7df7-7ccd-4902-8343-63852851d80c", "value": "A level of a building comprising all the rooms that are in it."}

{"id": "48d2f383-25f2-45b7-82d2-29d769247270", "value": "The space between two adjacent components, irrespective of whether it is filled with a jointing material or not."}
{"id": "3f2da0b4-d07d-4c2c-9b45-b8e9acddc8eb", "value": "A platform projecting from the wall of a building (on an upper level) and enclosed by a balustrade, a wall or bars."}
{"id": "f03557d5-67ef-4a3e-935a-853d5e67ed50", "value": "Components that belongs to the framework of a building or structure."}
{"id": "02fc9c50-e84a-4d69-9330-a447d6493c16", "value": "The upper covering of a building."}
{"id": "51e5269d-4674-4e28-ab64-01bdef8985e4", "value": "An opening in a outside wall or fence, which may be closed by a movable barrier, and made for the purpose of entrance and exit."}

{"id": "189d3ef6-4cf5-40cd-ad7c-24706dbbd31d", "value": "The solid ground or base (natural or built up, in the latter case usually constructed below the ground level) on which a building or other structure is erected."}
{"id": "806dd698-c6c4-42a0-84ed-b2b69c0909ea", "value": "A rounded vault forming the roof of a building or of a single room."}
{"id": "380afde7-a0b5-44c1-81c0-75085b126d1b", "value": "A low-pitched triangular part crowning the front of a building below the roof."}
{"id": "ab376d9d-6185-48b3-a4f1-b923037cc8cd", "value": "A covered structure in front of the entrance to a building, including a portico or a cover colonnade."}
{"id": "ccbc7ffd-e997-49f8-9052-7a2e09cabe67", "value": "A set of steps that lead from one level to another of a building, with or without a supporting structure."}
{"id": "72a1bf63-ae07-4a80-ab65-010343cba48b", "value": "A square or rectangular tall and vertical element projecting from a wall."}
{"id": "e464107d-9b40-446a-bc53-b58be944591c", "value": "The upper surface of the interior of a room."}
{"id": "389fb278-1a2a-40c1-9618-df9e90ae9112", "value": "The flat lower surface of the interior of a room or building."}
{"id": "7d099455-5d35-455c-9c07-9bf7b40f6bd5", "value": "A tall, vertical body (mostly cylindrical) used as support for some part of a building or sometimes used as mere decoration."}
{"id": "7f9caf5c-6e3a-47b5-b009-5366688128ab", "value": "An open pipe, or a shallow through fixed under the lower edge of a roof, or a simple channel, to collect and carry off the rainwater."}

{"id": "4aa39659-27db-4e78-9853-baa09c918d20", "value": "A moulding between the wall and the ceiling inside a building OR the horizontal projecting top-most part of the entablature which crowns or finishes a building or some part of a building."}
{"id": "7255b9c1-55a1-4895-8d38-8c6ab9c42199", "value": "Only to use when the cause is \"No Visible/Known\"."}

This category refers specifically to minor actions that do not impact on the structural integrity of the building, such as plaster, mosaics, or flooring."}
{"id": "648393b2-0cfc-473e-b2a3-fd70ad4f29ad", "value": "A new addition or extension is added to the building or heritage"}
